RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 48. Maiden Claiming Purse 6600. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOMEGROWN LEGEND rushed from outset, established an inside stance, set the pace in tandem, and refused to lose the stretch duel for the score. MISTER TYRO hustled from the break, was in concert for command, locked into a stretch duel, and was outdueled in final strides. OLD TOBY rated as the solo rival in the second flight, chased the front running duo while trekking the two path, and finished evenly for the show. CRYPTO MINER settled in behind rivals, trekked two wide around the bend, and was of little impact in the finish. RED ACE rated back and saved ground to no avail.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 77. Allowance Purse 17600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OKLAHOMA STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PEARLY hustled form outset and established a ground saving stance, led the field at every call and drew off in the end for a wire to wire score. CALI settled into mid pack in the early going, trekked three wide around the opening bend, tucked to save ground near the half way point, was roused inside the quarter pole, and earned the place but was no match for tough winner. KIMBELL'S STRATEGY showed reserve and gave chase to front runners while trekking the two path, swung wide rounding the final bend, and dug in for the show in homestrech. CON SUERTE was unhurried and trailed the field through the opening half, closed the gap on leaders along the backstretch, and came up empty in the closing strides. CANADA CANDY retreated rapidly in final stages after pressing the pace from a two path pose.

ENTRY.NAME: Cali
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide, inside at half, no match

ENTRY.NAME: Con Suerte
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, closed gap three eights, empty

ENTRY.NAME: Kimbell's Strategy
ENTRY.COMMENT: widest late, dug in for show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20460. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Horses That Started For a Claiming Price of $7,500 Or Less In Their Last Three Starts Least Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BABY LIAISON broke alertly, gained first command, set the pace as the inner most rival of three abreast, led every call, and inched away in the end for the wire to wire victory. HERO TIME hustled from outset to press the pace from a two path pose, rated close up along the backstretch and at upper stretch, but proved to e no match for winner in final sixteenth. TUFF MANDATE was unhurried through the openig half, swung to be widest of all at upper stretch, and rallied mildly to share the show. MAJESTIC LOVER pressed the pace from outset as the widest of three abreast through the opening half before fading in closing strides. STOLEN GHOST trekked three wide throughout and was no threat to top three. TRUE DOMINUS tucked to the inside shortly after the start, saved ground all the way, and failed to menace.

ENTRY.NAME: dh-Tuff Mandate
ENTRY.COMMENT: widest of all, shared the show

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 6600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: G KATE hustled form outset and led the field in concert from a two path pose, trekked the inside path around the final turn, locked into a stretch duel and proved best in the end. SHACKLELACKALACKA trekked wide early while sharing command, led the field in tandem along the backstretch, was two wide at upper stretch, then bested in the stretch duel for the honors. ACERTIVE MISS pressed the early pace as the inner most rival of four abreast around the opening turn, backed out of the bid near the three eighths pole, maintained an inside stance, and rallied along the rail to get up for the show. LOVELY LOLITA broke alertly, pressed the pace from a two path pose, dropped back to second flight inside the quarter pole, and finished willingly to be gaining on leaders at finish. MISS M J failed to rally after settling in behind rivals nd giving chase from a three path stance. EVENING STORM failed to threaten from a trailing position.

ENTRY.NAME: Acertive Miss
ENTRY.OWNER: Parsley, Jean Ann and James Oakley
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside,backed out three eighths,rail rally, up for show

ENTRY.NAME: Lovely Lolita
ENTRY.COMMENT: two wide journey, gaining at finish

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 87. Allowance Purse 19250. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of $30,000 At A Mile Or Over In 2022 - 2023 Allowed 3 lbs. (Multiple Winners Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOMMYHAWK showed reserve in the opening half, split foes while under urging along the backstretch, angled out at upper stretch and rallied for the score. ABSAROKA hustled from outset and led the field in tandem while trekking the inside lane, led the field at upper stretch, but couldnt fend off the late rally of eventual winner in final sixteenth. ROWDY RASCAL trekked two wide, led the field briefly near the quarter pole, and weakened in the crucial strides. BOX SEAT settled into second flight and chased the pacesetting duo from a three wide pose, was roused inside the quarter pole and gained mildly in the late stages. UNRESTRICTED lacked a needed late kick after tucking to the inside and giving chase from second flight.

ENTRY.NAME: Tommyhawk
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, split foes, angled out, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Absaroka
ENTRY.OWNER: Covey Seth and Caldwell J R

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 61. Claiming Purse 7150. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ELUSIVE FREUD showed reserve and loomed behind the pacesetting duo around the first turn, responded to urging in closing bend, swung wide at upper stretch, and got up in time for the score. SPEND AGAIN hustled from the break and led the field from a two path pose through the opening half, had a slight advantage at upper stretch, was met with a challenge near the sixteenth pole, and was nailed at wire for the score. BLAKE FROM TISH was unhurried through the opening half, closed the gap on front runners inside the quarter pole and rallied to duel in the final sixteenth between rivals. SCHLEICHER trailed the field from outset and passed tiring rival in closing strides. MACER THE RACER rushed form outset to lead the field in concert as the inside rival, backed out of the bid at upper stretch, and faded rapidly in final furlong. AFTER AN INQUIRY, THE BOARD OF STEWARDS DISQUALIFIED 5:SPEND AGAIN FROM SECOND PLACE AND PLACED HIM THIRD

ENTRY.NAME: Elusive Freud
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, three wide upper, in time

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Spend Again
ENTRY.OWNER: Hookstra Terry and Pickering James W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 82. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 6600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $5,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CANEY'S GHOST came away alertly, trekked five wide early, rated three wide at the halfway point, led the field along the backstretch and proved best in the stretch duel for the score. WIN FOR FUN broke alertly, established an inside position, led the field in tandem, then was edged in the stretch duel. JACKS SPRING BREAK was unhurried in early strides, angled out along the backstretch and advanced on the leaders, then tucked to save ground at upper stretch adn rallied to earn the show. ROCKPORT KAT settled into mid pack, saved ground near the midway point, angled out at upper stretch, and finished evenly. NOMOREMRNICEGUY trekked widest of all through the opening half, rated mid pack at upper stretch, and failed to produce a closing bid. ELECTORAL failed to menace while travelling wide throughout. SEDARIS chased rivals around the opening bend, swung to four wide after first call, trekked four wide to the quarter pole, rated back at upper stretch and tired in closing strides. TOUGH COMPANY pressed the early pce from a two path stance, lost ground to front runners along the backstretch, and retreated in crucial stages.

ENTRY.NAME: Caney's Ghost
ENTRY.COMMENT: five wide, three wide, best in duel

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FAIR MEADOWS RACE 8 6F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Special Weight Purse 20460. FOR ACCREDITED OKLAHOMA-BREDS MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Horses That Started For a Claiming Price of $7,500 Or Less In Their Last Three Starts Least Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MAJESTIC LIAISON broke on top, led the field at every call and steadily widened the margin for a gate to wire score. JOE BILL gave chase from a four wide pose, rated as the lose rival in second flight at upper stretch, and finished a clear second but was no match for runaway winner. SON OF PREACHERMAN showed reserve early, was roused nearing the quarter pole, responded well and improved placing in the late going. IN BOND WE TRUST travelled three wide early, led the second flight at the quarter pole, saved ground at upper stretch, but couldnt catch the front runners in final furlong. MAJESTIC FLASH settled into mid pack and trekked a ground saving path around the first turn, lost ground to front runners near the quarter pole, trekked the three path at upper stretch and tired in late stages. HELLRAZER trailed from outset and failed to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Majestic Flash
ENTRY.COMMENT: inside second flight, three path upper, tired

ENTRY.NAME: In Bond We Trust
ENTRY.OWNER: Higgins William H and Davidson M Brent
ENTRY.COMMENT: three wide early, inside upper, couldnt ctch
